The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and adversarial attacks in the context of accounting and auditing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models (cs.AI) and deep learning techniques (cs.LG) to generate adversarial examples. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of these attacks on the finance and accounting domain, which could fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
